        "id": 1114919
      },
      "writtenOn": "2020-07-30T05:44:19Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I\u0027m tandrii and I\u0027m again asking you about the locks 😄 sorry.\n\niiuc, this is the only thing that has to be locked. Can this be done up front for all tasks before all the hashing + serialization?\n\n\nAfter more thought: why do we need to lock clsByTyp at all? Isn\u0027t it OK to distinctly limit dispatcher\u0027s lifetime to two phases: \n * registration (mutable) \n * serving (immutable)\n?\n\nOn pods/services where InstallRoutes is called, that\u0027s a natural boundary.\nOn pods/services which only AddTasks, I guess a Finalize() or Freeze() can be added.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 478,
        "startChar": 1,
        "endLine": 481,
        "endChar": 2
      },
      "revId": "8d49f51bc39b05353b59a49a1eaf5f7ca8f478c7",
      "serverId": "3ce6091f-6c88-37e8-8c75-72f92ae8dfba",
      "unresolved": true
